data.value:
Excess weight can put you at increased risk of health issues such as type 2 diabetes, heart disease, stroke.
Working towards a healthier weight and keeping the weight off can help reduce your risk of health problems in the longer term.
Your health could benefit from losing 5% of your weight.
Aim to lose 4kg Recommended daily calorie intake: 1868 - 2402 kcal To lose 1-2lbs a week stick to the lower end of the range.

data.name: label9.Text
data.value: It has been a tough 18-month road, which has included 28 chemotherapy treatments, two back-to-back surgeries, and radiation — and it continues indefinitely. But I just received news on March 1, 2016 (the first day of Colon Cancer Awareness Month), that I had no evidence of disease in my body. As my oncologist exclaimed, “It’s nothing short of a miracle.” Finally looking up from my battle, I have to agree.

data.name: label12.Text
data.value: While we hope for a long and healthy life, it is always best to be prepared for whatever that comes our way, even something as tragic as a critical illness. With AIA CI, I was supported financially so my family and I can focus on my recovery.
